The article is a statement by President Obama and Mrs. Obama on Nelson Mandela International Day. They congratulate Nelson Mandela on his 93rd birthday and honor his vision for a better world. Mandela's legacy exemplifies wisdom, strength, and grace. The United States joined other United Nations member states in creating Nelson Mandela International Day in 2009, and on July 18, the global community celebrates Mandela through acts of service. Mandela's life showed the path to justice, reconciliation, and democracy.